It is a fundamental aspect of quantum mechanics, and it has been observed in a wide range of physical systems, including the behavior of electrons in semiconductors and the decay of radioactive nuclei.

In summary, while quantum tunneling is a fundamental aspect of quantum mechanics, it is not possible for a quantum tunneling event to create a new person.
